WEBVTT

00:07.130 --> 00:08.930
VALENCE:
It's alphanumeric.

00:09.130 --> 00:10.700
There's only one way
it would work on that dial.

00:13.270 --> 00:14.180
<i>WEIR:</i>
<i>Is this real?</i>

00:15.880 --> 00:17.280
Seventh century.

00:17.480 --> 00:19.370
B.C.E., of course.

00:19.570 --> 00:21.980
I'm sorry. I must've said it
a thousand times.

00:22.180 --> 00:24.160
No, actually, this is the
first time you've said it.

00:24.360 --> 00:25.680
<i>Blackmail will not work.</i>

00:25.880 --> 00:27.600
<i> My marriage was over years ago.</i>

00:27.800 --> 00:29.080
Somebody has been
illegally feeding

00:29.280 --> 00:30.730
you and your campaign
millions of dollars,

00:30.930 --> 00:32.210
<i>and we can prove it.</i>
<i>If we helped you get</i>

00:32.410 --> 00:33.820
your case back,
would you help us?

00:34.020 --> 00:35.000
Yes.

00:35.200 --> 00:37.080
- So, what's my part?
- Nothing.

00:37.280 --> 00:38.160
You're cutting me out?

00:39.640 --> 00:40.960
WEIR:
As long as you stick
to the prescribed route,

00:41.160 --> 00:42.870
<i>none of the alarms</i>
<i>get activated.</i>

00:43.070 --> 00:45.270
Sensor error. Reset. Reset.

00:45.470 --> 00:46.920
HAILEY:
We're good.

00:47.120 --> 00:48.310
BEN:
We developed techniques on how

00:48.510 --> 00:49.580
to manipulate populations.

00:49.770 --> 00:51.360
The Algorithms of Control.

00:51.560 --> 00:53.190
Did he have any proof?

00:53.390 --> 00:55.620
He said he had a guy who was
bringing him proof, who was on

00:55.820 --> 00:57.540
<i>the AeroDelhi flight</i>
<i>disappeared last year.</i>

00:57.740 --> 00:59.020
<i>...disappearance</i>
<i>have not been resolved,</i>

00:59.220 --> 01:00.410
<i>and terrorism</i>
<i>has not been ruled out.</i>

01:00.610 --> 01:02.060
Are you in position?

01:03.280 --> 01:05.110
- I'll be there.
- [gunshot]

01:05.310 --> 01:07.110
<i>HOMM:</i>
<i>Why would Crowley</i>
<i>kill his own candidate?</i>

01:07.310 --> 01:08.550
<i>WEIR:</i>
<i>'Cause this wasn't about</i>
<i>winning the presidency.</i>

01:08.750 --> 01:10.680
This was about passing the
Shared Data Act.

01:10.880 --> 01:11.990
When that happens,

01:12.190 --> 01:13.690
Crowley gains access
to thousands

01:13.890 --> 01:15.730
of data points
on every single American.

01:15.930 --> 01:18.340
And with that,
he can control anyone.

01:18.540 --> 01:21.090
<i>BEN:</i>
<i>He wants power.</i>
<i>He wants a regime of his own,</i>

01:21.280 --> 01:23.610
and he wants it right here.

01:23.810 --> 01:25.180
<i>HAILEY:</i>
<i>You think he's trying</i>
<i>to reach Valence?</i>

01:25.380 --> 01:28.010
Maybe he had
a back channel going.

01:28.200 --> 01:29.570
Emailing a dead friend

01:29.770 --> 01:32.260
<i>is a level beyond exhaustion.</i>

01:36.350 --> 01:38.010
<i>VALENCE:</i>
<i>Tell them I had no choice.</i>

01:39.660 --> 01:40.920
Miles, no!

01:51.410 --> 01:54.030
<i>In the wake</i>
<i>of the shocking assassination</i>

01:54.230 --> 01:55.680
<i>of Senator Nora Evers,</i>

01:55.880 --> 01:57.470
<i>a groundswell of support</i>
<i>has propelled</i>

01:57.670 --> 01:59.650
<i>her controversial</i>
<i>Shared Data Bill</i>

01:59.840 --> 02:01.780
<i>to an early vote</i>
<i>on the Senate floor.</i>

02:01.980 --> 02:05.130
<i> Renamed in her honor, the Nora </i>
<i> Evers American Protection Act</i>

02:05.330 --> 02:07.260
<i>will allow select</i>
<i>private companies</i>

02:07.460 --> 02:09.660
<i>access to U.S. citizens'</i>
<i>government records</i>

02:09.850 --> 02:11.440
<i>and consumer data.</i>

02:11.640 --> 02:14.180
<i>Nora Evers' Shared Data Act</i>
<i>is expected to pass</i>

02:14.380 --> 02:16.620
<i>by an overwhelming margin</i>
<i>in two days.</i>

02:16.820 --> 02:18.840
<i>The president has promised</i>
<i>to sign it that day,</i>

02:19.040 --> 02:20.970
<i>at which point the U.S. </i>
<i> government will begin to share</i>

02:21.170 --> 02:24.240
<i>all of its data acquisition</i>
<i>and monitoring resources</i>

02:24.430 --> 02:27.460
<i>with three private technology</i>
<i>firms selected by Congress:</i>

02:27.660 --> 02:30.020
<i>Termina Systems, CKB Digital,</i>

02:30.220 --> 02:32.240
<i>and Arda Analytics.</i>

02:32.440 --> 02:34.630
<i>In other news...</i>

02:35.280 --> 02:37.470
♪

02:37.670 --> 02:39.630
<i>[indistinct, overlapping</i>
<i>news broadcasts]</i>

02:51.510 --> 02:54.600
["Blind Vision"
by Blancmange playing]

02:56.950 --> 02:58.360
♪ <i>Blind hope</i>♪

02:58.560 --> 03:01.010
♪ <i>Blind visions</i>♪

03:01.210 --> 03:02.750
♪ <i>Blind center</i>♪

03:02.950 --> 03:05.010
♪ <i>One center</i>♪

03:05.210 --> 03:06.540
♪ <i>Blind living</i>♪

03:06.740 --> 03:08.710
♪ <i>And seeing</i>♪

03:08.910 --> 03:11.500
♪ <i>Blind hell, blind hell</i>♪

03:11.700 --> 03:14.590
♪ <i>Blind visions</i>♪

03:14.790 --> 03:17.980
♪ <i>And no reasons for action</i>♪

03:18.180 --> 03:19.990
♪ <i>Blind words...</i>♪

03:20.190 --> 03:21.680
- [kids clamoring]
- Run.

03:21.880 --> 03:23.690
- John.
- What the hell, Weir?

03:23.890 --> 03:25.990
- Don't talk about my father.
- What? I didn't!

03:26.190 --> 03:28.950
- Bullshit.
- John. John.

03:29.150 --> 03:31.610
- That son of a bitch was
telling people that my dad...
- No, I haven't.

03:31.810 --> 03:34.570
Weir, you're fucking crazy.

03:34.770 --> 03:36.570
John, John. Gilgamesh.

03:36.770 --> 03:38.140
Gilgamesh?

03:38.330 --> 03:40.700
It's in two hours.
We have to study.

03:40.900 --> 03:42.700
Oh, shit.

03:42.900 --> 03:44.790
Let's go.

03:44.990 --> 03:47.840
- What'd he say about your dad?
- Nothing, but he was
thinking it.

03:48.040 --> 03:49.280
<i>VALENCE:</i>
<i>Listen, you can't have</i>

03:49.480 --> 03:52.710
assholes like that
get in your head.

03:52.910 --> 03:57.110
You have to focus
on what really matters to you.

03:57.310 --> 03:59.420
"When two go together,
each will protect himself

03:59.620 --> 04:01.680
and shield his companion."

04:01.880 --> 04:05.070
"And when they fall,
they'll leave an enduring name."

04:05.270 --> 04:06.730
BOTH:
"Today,

04:06.930 --> 04:09.340
"give me your aid,
and you shall have mine.

04:09.540 --> 04:12.040
What then can go amiss
with us two?"

04:12.240 --> 04:13.260
See?

04:13.460 --> 04:15.260
I'm focused.

04:15.460 --> 04:18.250
Yeah. Thanks to me.

04:21.260 --> 04:23.440
<i>HOMM:</i>
<i>I got to be honest.</i>

04:23.640 --> 04:25.660
This is a little disappointing.

04:25.860 --> 04:27.310
BEN:
Where's the pornography?

04:27.510 --> 04:29.580
WEIR:
There is no pornography.
She lied to us.

04:29.780 --> 04:32.710
She wanted what was in the case,
and she used us to get it.

04:32.910 --> 04:34.670
These are just
a bunch of numbers.

04:34.870 --> 04:36.720
- Fuck.
- Why would Evers go to
so much trouble to get this?

04:36.910 --> 04:39.500
Evers didn't do shit.
We went to so much trouble.

04:39.700 --> 04:41.420
WEIR:
Well, clearly she wanted it,

04:41.620 --> 04:43.630
- so it's got to be worth
something, but why?
- I don't know.

04:46.060 --> 04:48.680
<i>HOMM:</i>
<i>I got to be honest.</i>

04:48.880 --> 04:50.770
This is a little disappointing.

04:50.970 --> 04:52.250
HAILEY:
These are just
a bunch of numbers.

04:52.450 --> 04:54.430
HOMM:
Maybe the Kompromat

04:54.630 --> 04:56.740
wasn't sexual,
maybe it was financial.

04:56.930 --> 04:59.430
She stole a bunch of money,
and this is the evidence?

04:59.630 --> 05:00.990
I'd, I'd buy that.

05:01.990 --> 05:04.660
<i>HOMM:</i>
<i>I got to be honest.</i>

05:04.860 --> 05:07.090
This is a little disappointing.

05:07.290 --> 05:08.440
BEN:
You're all missing the point.

05:08.640 --> 05:10.620
This briefcase
was just a distraction

05:10.820 --> 05:13.930
to keep you busy
while I pursued my actual goal.

05:14.130 --> 05:16.060
What is your actual goal?

05:16.260 --> 05:19.310
Helping my friend
pass the Data Act.

05:21.790 --> 05:24.460
<i>HOMM:</i>
<i>I got to be honest.</i>

05:24.660 --> 05:27.200
This is a little disappointing.

05:27.400 --> 05:28.810
You think you can
make sense of this?

05:29.010 --> 05:30.680
HOMM:
Uh, I don't know.
Two digits, a dash,

05:30.880 --> 05:32.340
s-s-seven digits.

05:32.540 --> 05:34.690
Those are probably
corporate I.D. numbers.

05:34.890 --> 05:36.300
And these 12-digit numbers
could be LLCs.

05:36.500 --> 05:37.860
How long would it take you

05:38.060 --> 05:39.430
- to identify all of them?
- John, we have to accept

05:39.630 --> 05:41.520
there might not be
enough time for that.

05:41.720 --> 05:43.220
What'd you just say?
Not enough time?

05:43.420 --> 05:44.650
The president's gonna
sign that bill in two days.

05:44.850 --> 05:46.180
It's gonna take Homm
that long just to...

05:46.380 --> 05:47.790
What-what are we supposed to do?
Just give up?

05:47.990 --> 05:50.270
No, of course not.
Johnathan, listen to me.

05:50.470 --> 05:51.750
Look, all I've done
is listen to you for five years.

05:51.950 --> 05:53.180
All you've said is, we got to

05:53.380 --> 05:54.230
stop Crowley,
we got to stop Crowley,

05:54.430 --> 05:55.490
or he'll take down America.

05:55.690 --> 05:57.140
People have died
trying to stop him.

05:57.340 --> 05:58.410
My friends are dead.
My fucking friends are dead!

05:58.610 --> 06:00.150
Calm down.

06:00.350 --> 06:02.060
Now you say you want
the Data Act to pass?

06:02.260 --> 06:03.370
What? I...

06:03.570 --> 06:05.450
Weir, he never said that.

06:16.110 --> 06:17.630
[sighs]

06:35.780 --> 06:37.480
[typing]

06:48.400 --> 06:50.070
Ugh, gross.

06:50.270 --> 06:52.760
Mom.

06:52.960 --> 06:54.770
Don't you have
a printer at work?

06:54.970 --> 06:58.470
- Not for this stuff.
- What happened to them?

06:58.670 --> 07:00.900
Uh, they didn't finish
their school applications.

07:01.100 --> 07:02.950
What do you think
I was printing out?

07:03.150 --> 07:04.340
Why did you and Mom
even have me?

07:04.540 --> 07:05.730
Just to be mean to me
all the time?

07:05.930 --> 07:08.350
All right. Check your essay
for typos.

07:08.540 --> 07:11.990
- God, Mom, I am.
- [printer whirs]

07:21.260 --> 07:23.580
What are you up to, you asshole?

07:23.780 --> 07:25.740
<i>[scanner whirring]</i>

07:32.530 --> 07:34.630
- Where are you going?
- [sighs]

07:34.830 --> 07:37.290
One of us needs to check on him.

07:37.490 --> 07:39.900
No, just...
don't-don't wake him up.

07:40.100 --> 07:41.640
I've literally
never seen him sleep.

07:41.840 --> 07:42.680
[sighs]

07:42.880 --> 07:44.420
Just leave him be.

07:44.620 --> 07:46.560
Do they teach avoidance
at the psychiatrist school?

07:46.760 --> 07:49.040
[scoffs] Psychology.

07:49.240 --> 07:51.170
And he is the one
who's avoiding me, so...

07:51.370 --> 07:54.870
So what? He's falling apart.

07:55.070 --> 07:56.610
[sighs]

07:56.810 --> 07:59.480
Listen, at the moment,
he considers me to be the cause

07:59.680 --> 08:01.700
of whatever ails him
rather than the cure,

08:01.900 --> 08:05.100
so it would be better
if we just left him alone.

08:05.300 --> 08:07.400
More gems of parenting wisdom.

08:07.600 --> 08:10.230
- You make any sense of this lot?
- Actually, yeah.

08:10.430 --> 08:12.280
We got their
corporate I.D. numbers

08:12.480 --> 08:14.370
and the bank routing numbers.

08:14.570 --> 08:17.460
This-this is a regional code.

08:17.660 --> 08:19.330
- HAILEY: Guys.
- It's the same as this number.

08:19.530 --> 08:21.330
- He's gone.
- BEN: Fuck.

08:21.530 --> 08:23.030
- HOMM: What?
- [sighs]

08:23.230 --> 08:25.060
Oh, man.

08:26.720 --> 08:27.600
- Weir!
- Homm.

08:27.800 --> 08:28.730
- Oh, goddamn.
- What...

08:28.930 --> 08:29.950
Homm, get away from the window.

08:30.150 --> 08:31.730
- Get over here.
- Oh. Sorry.

08:31.930 --> 08:33.430
I...

08:33.630 --> 08:35.160
I'm not used to being
a fugitive.

08:43.000 --> 08:44.740
Sorry.

09:01.450 --> 09:03.070
<i>NEWSWOMAN: Murder suspect </i>
<i> John Weir is still on the loos.</i>

09:03.270 --> 09:05.030
<i>The public is urged</i>
<i>to contact the authorities</i>

09:05.230 --> 09:06.810
<i>with any information</i>
<i>about the suspect</i>

09:07.010 --> 09:08.810
<i>and any recent</i>
<i>known whereabouts.</i>

09:09.010 --> 09:10.980
<i>[indistinct</i>
<i>police radio chatter]</i>

09:34.220 --> 09:35.870
Welcome to Bart's.

09:58.940 --> 10:01.520
He's not picking up his phone.

10:01.720 --> 10:03.080
HOMM:
Uh, where are you going?

10:03.280 --> 10:05.570
To find him.

10:05.770 --> 10:07.440
Good luck.

10:07.640 --> 10:11.050
Jesus, Ben, aren't you a little
bit worried about him? Your son?

10:11.250 --> 10:13.700
I worry about him all the time.

10:17.700 --> 10:20.230
- Where will you even look?
- I don't know.

10:20.430 --> 10:21.830
Maybe he went to his ex-wife's.

10:23.750 --> 10:25.450
I didn't know Weir
even had an ex.

10:25.650 --> 10:27.940
Uh, Ben, do you have
her phone number?

10:28.140 --> 10:30.590
- What? Um...
- So she...

10:30.790 --> 10:32.070
No.

10:32.270 --> 10:33.900
No. We were never very close.

10:34.100 --> 10:35.900
Well, he can't have gone far,

10:36.100 --> 10:37.600
unless he took the van,
which is, I guess,

10:37.800 --> 10:39.110
where I'll start.

10:41.680 --> 10:43.250
[sighs]

11:08.710 --> 11:11.200
[computer chimes]

11:11.400 --> 11:13.110
Once we're granted access
to the data,

11:13.310 --> 11:14.630
we've got teams standing by to
start filtering it immediately.

11:14.830 --> 11:15.760
Hang on.

11:18.240 --> 11:19.680
[chuckles]

11:19.880 --> 11:21.860
He's not even wearing a hat.

11:22.060 --> 11:24.600
He's either playing poker
or pumping nickel slots.

11:24.800 --> 11:26.860
And he's logged in
without using a VPN.

11:27.060 --> 11:28.870
It's almost like
he wants to get caught.

11:29.070 --> 11:30.390
Well, oblige him.

11:30.590 --> 11:33.220
Only don't underestimate
this guy this time.

11:33.420 --> 11:35.960
Let the cops go in first. Good?

11:36.160 --> 11:39.050
<i>DISPATCHER:</i>
<i>All units, all units. 25420.</i>

11:39.250 --> 11:41.910
<i>98% match--</i>
<i>murder suspect John Weir.</i>

11:55.800 --> 11:57.800
[phone buzzing]

12:02.540 --> 12:04.030
Hey.

12:04.230 --> 12:05.730
<i>I'm sorry I took off</i>
<i>without telling you,</i>

12:05.930 --> 12:07.590
<i>but I need to do this alone.</i>

12:08.980 --> 12:10.600
- Do what?
<i>- WOMAN: Attention, Bart's...</i>

12:10.800 --> 12:12.470
Look, we shouldn't be
using phones right now, okay?

12:12.670 --> 12:13.910
<i> HAILEY: Tell me where you are,</i>
<i>and we won't need to.</i>

12:14.110 --> 12:15.610
Can't do that.

12:15.810 --> 12:17.440
- Weir, we don't have
a lot of time.
<i>- I know,</i>

12:17.640 --> 12:18.700
and I'm trying
to find some answers,

12:18.900 --> 12:19.870
and I can do it faster
on my own.

12:20.070 --> 12:20.960
<i>Answers to what?</i>

12:21.160 --> 12:22.180
Okay, Hailey, I'm hanging up.

12:22.380 --> 12:24.040
<i>Don't. Please. Weir, talk...</i>

12:28.960 --> 12:30.970
<i>- HAILEY: Do what?</i>
<i>- WOMAN: Attention,</i>
<i>Bart's Platinum Members...</i>

12:31.170 --> 12:33.020
<i>WEIR:</i>
<i>We shouldn't be using</i>
<i>phones right now, okay?</i>

12:33.220 --> 12:34.710
<i>HAILEY:</i>
<i>Tell me where you are,</i>
<i>and we won't need to.</i>

12:34.910 --> 12:36.060
<i>WOMAN: Attention,</i>
<i>Bart's Platinum Members...</i>

12:36.260 --> 12:39.410
- [sirens wailing]
- [tires screeching]

13:00.250 --> 13:02.210
♪

13:22.880 --> 13:23.930
[mutters]

13:29.500 --> 13:32.210
Excuse me. I need your help
over here, please.

13:32.410 --> 13:33.940
Uh, yeah.

13:46.650 --> 13:48.220
Buddy, how are you?

13:48.420 --> 13:50.530
Dude, you got a problem?

13:50.730 --> 13:53.480
I'm sorry, thought I recognized
you from high school. Sorry.

13:56.000 --> 13:58.490
Can I get an HDMI cable, please?

13:58.690 --> 14:00.320
[security sensors beeping]

14:00.520 --> 14:02.370
Uh, excuse me, sir. I'm just
gonna have to check your bags.

14:02.570 --> 14:04.410
What the hell? I got a receipt
for everything.

14:04.610 --> 14:05.940
Just doing my job, sir. Hold on.

14:06.140 --> 14:08.100
[sirens wailing]

14:17.290 --> 14:19.470
- Weir. Oh.
- Jesus Christ.

14:19.670 --> 14:21.910
How the fuck did you find me?

14:22.110 --> 14:23.740
I'm smart. I heard
Bart's P.A. announcement

14:23.940 --> 14:25.220
in the background
when we were on the phone.

14:25.420 --> 14:27.700
Shit. Does Ben know
you're looking for me?

14:27.900 --> 14:29.790
Does he know you're following
me? Are you working with him?

14:29.990 --> 14:31.830
- What is going on
with you, Weir?
- Nothing.

14:32.030 --> 14:34.360
- I know that's not true.
- Oh, please, honestly.

14:34.560 --> 14:35.880
You're not yourself right now.
You're paranoid.

14:36.080 --> 14:37.490
No, no, no.

14:37.690 --> 14:39.400
Paranoid is delusional.
What I'm dealing with,

14:39.600 --> 14:41.710
- not delusional.
- Really? You accused

14:41.910 --> 14:43.970
Ben of saying he wanted
the Data Act to pass.

14:44.170 --> 14:45.240
- I know.
- He never said that.

14:45.440 --> 14:46.890
I know.

14:47.090 --> 14:49.070
But in my mind, there's
a version of him that did.

14:49.270 --> 14:51.020
What?

14:51.220 --> 14:54.320
It's-it's how my mind works,
okay? I-It's complicated.

14:55.110 --> 14:57.070
If I can't find
a rational explanation

14:57.270 --> 14:58.120
for what's happening around me,

14:58.320 --> 14:59.820
my mind just starts to visualize

15:00.020 --> 15:01.330
every other possible scenario.

15:02.640 --> 15:04.690
Until it finds
the most logical one.

15:04.890 --> 15:06.560
<i>But every now and then,</i>

15:06.760 --> 15:08.550
I can't control it.

15:09.770 --> 15:13.170
Valence knew how to pull me out.
He knew what to say.

15:14.470 --> 15:16.700
[distant siren wailing]

15:16.900 --> 15:19.310
But he's not here
right now, so, uh...

15:19.510 --> 15:22.230
I'm having a little difficult
time knowing what's really real.

15:22.430 --> 15:25.220
Seriously?

15:35.890 --> 15:37.460
Shit.

15:37.660 --> 15:38.900
Behind me.

15:39.100 --> 15:41.030
Unmarked gray SUV.

15:41.230 --> 15:42.900
I thought I kept my head down.
Come on.

15:43.100 --> 15:44.470
- It's just a guy...
- We got to catch this bus.
Come on.

15:44.670 --> 15:46.690
Go, go, go.

15:46.890 --> 15:49.690
All the way in the back.

15:49.890 --> 15:51.300
HAILEY:
Weir!

15:51.500 --> 15:54.120
Stop the bus. Weir!
I need to get off.

16:06.660 --> 16:08.140
You're late.

16:09.790 --> 16:13.370
I took measures to make sure
I wasn't followed.

16:13.570 --> 16:15.010
So...

16:17.230 --> 16:19.290
The next time,
I suggest you leave some space

16:19.490 --> 16:22.500
in your planning to accommodate
these measures, no?

16:24.110 --> 16:26.600
- Hi.
- HAILEY: Hi.

16:26.800 --> 16:29.460
Hey, um, who's the man?

16:31.070 --> 16:32.390
What? W-Which man?

16:32.590 --> 16:33.910
HOMM:
[stammers] Who's the man?

16:34.110 --> 16:37.300
- Homm is the man.
- [laughs]

16:37.500 --> 16:39.220
[chuckles]

16:39.420 --> 16:41.610
Oh, did you figure out the stuff
in the briefcase?

16:41.810 --> 16:44.220
- Yeah. [laughs]
- Yeah?

16:44.420 --> 16:47.840
It's-it's a road map
to Crowley's operation. A...

16:48.040 --> 16:49.880
Rosetta Stone of corruption.

16:50.080 --> 16:51.580
Shell companies, bank accounts,

16:51.780 --> 16:53.320
routing numbers,
Social Security numbers.

16:53.520 --> 16:55.500
Everyone who Crowley owns.

16:55.700 --> 16:57.540
HOMM:
And it's a real who's who.

16:57.740 --> 17:00.110
Uh, politicians, CEOs,
journalists,

17:00.310 --> 17:02.500
two Supreme Court judges.

17:02.700 --> 17:04.380
- And Crowley owns them?
- BEN: Mm-hmm.

17:04.570 --> 17:05.460
How?

17:05.660 --> 17:07.770
Blackmail.

17:07.970 --> 17:09.990
Or probably got
a few of them, uh, followers

17:10.190 --> 17:12.340
of the gospel according
to Crowley anyway.

17:12.540 --> 17:14.780
Plus, he pays them a lot.

17:14.980 --> 17:16.430
- HAILEY: Must've cost a fortune.
- Yeah, he doesn't give a shit

17:16.630 --> 17:18.350
about that. It's the control.

17:18.550 --> 17:21.130
Same as Evers. That's probably
why she wanted the case so bad.

17:21.330 --> 17:22.960
She wasn't afraid of it
embarrassing her.

17:23.160 --> 17:24.400
She wanted it for herself

17:24.590 --> 17:27.620
'cause whoever has this info
controls...

17:27.820 --> 17:29.490
everything.

17:29.690 --> 17:31.270
So, who do we bring it to?

17:31.470 --> 17:32.880
BEN:
We can't bring it to anyone.

17:33.080 --> 17:35.190
HAILEY:
Why the fuck not?
Let's end this.

17:35.390 --> 17:36.490
Um...

17:36.690 --> 17:39.060
Wh... What?

17:39.260 --> 17:40.930
Well, it's... I mean, it's just,

17:41.130 --> 17:42.330
with all the powerful people
on this list,

17:42.530 --> 17:44.760
whoever we deliver it to,
might just

17:44.960 --> 17:46.240
turn it back over to Crowley.

17:46.440 --> 17:49.640
So, then what was the plan?
What was this

17:49.840 --> 17:52.730
great plan that we've all been
sticking to all along?

17:52.930 --> 17:53.990
There might still be a play.

17:54.190 --> 17:55.470
- [scoffs]
- BEN: I-I suggest

17:55.670 --> 17:57.430
- we wait for Johnathan.
- HAILEY: Oh, well,

17:57.630 --> 17:59.040
if the plan is waiting for Weir,

17:59.240 --> 18:00.870
then we're all fucked.

18:01.070 --> 18:03.430
[footsteps retreat]

18:03.630 --> 18:06.250
[doorbell rings]

18:33.500 --> 18:36.210
I... I need help.

18:36.410 --> 18:38.900
I don't have anyone to talk to,
and I need to talk.

18:39.100 --> 18:42.650
If I just go over things
in my mind, I...

18:42.850 --> 18:45.000
I get lost, and I...

18:45.200 --> 18:47.040
PRIEST:
We all get a little lost.

18:47.240 --> 18:50.440
Jesus, I don't mean like that.
I mean.... [sighs]

18:50.640 --> 18:53.180
lost, like I literally
can't tell the difference

18:53.380 --> 18:56.010
between what's real
and what's not.

18:56.210 --> 18:58.400
Somehow, talking out loud helps.

18:58.600 --> 19:01.270
I-I haven't slept for days.

19:01.470 --> 19:03.060
This time,

19:03.260 --> 19:05.630
there may have been too many
possibilities, too many...

19:05.830 --> 19:07.490
motivations, I...

19:09.010 --> 19:11.150
I used to have a friend
that would help me

19:11.350 --> 19:13.070
get through times
like this, but he died.

19:13.270 --> 19:14.590
PRIEST:
I'm very sorry.

19:14.790 --> 19:16.890
Is there anyone else
you're close to?

19:19.630 --> 19:21.640
In my line of work,

19:21.840 --> 19:23.860
it's best not to get close
to anyone.

19:24.060 --> 19:25.260
PRIEST:
That sounds lonely.

19:25.450 --> 19:27.430
Yeah.

19:27.630 --> 19:29.650
Look, I didn't come here
for some kind of console

19:29.850 --> 19:33.050
or salvation or Hail Marys
or whatever it is you do.

19:33.250 --> 19:35.400
I-I just need someone to listen.

19:35.600 --> 19:37.050
Do you think you can do that?
Just-just listen

19:37.250 --> 19:38.490
and keep it between us?

19:38.690 --> 19:40.880
PRIEST:
Just us and God.

19:41.080 --> 19:43.660
[scoffs] God.

19:43.860 --> 19:45.190
Great. Well,
maybe he can tell me

19:45.390 --> 19:47.890
what the fuck
is going on because...

19:48.090 --> 19:49.890
I don't have a lot of time.
Two days, tops.

19:50.090 --> 19:51.460
And I need to know
what's happening, what's real,

19:51.650 --> 19:52.890
or we're all fucked.

19:53.090 --> 19:54.980
I got my friend--
my only friend--

19:55.180 --> 19:56.720
trying to tell me that
my father's been lying to me

19:56.920 --> 19:59.160
- this whole time, and...
- PRIEST: Your friend?

19:59.360 --> 20:01.470
The dead one. Look, in my heart,
I know he's dead, okay?

20:01.660 --> 20:03.380
I watched him jump.
I saw his face.

20:03.580 --> 20:05.250
But what if it's just a setup?
What if, what if it isn't real?

20:05.450 --> 20:07.210
What if he's still alive, and
he's trying to warn me and...

20:07.410 --> 20:09.470
- [phone ringing]
- [sighs]

20:09.670 --> 20:11.690
Goddamn it.

20:11.890 --> 20:14.960
Sorry, Father. Excuse me.

20:15.160 --> 20:16.740
Midtown Television Repair.

20:16.940 --> 20:18.570
<i>LIV [over phone]:</i>
<i>John, it's me.</i>

20:18.770 --> 20:20.350
Look, I know I'm not
supposed to call,

20:20.550 --> 20:23.130
but a package
came in the mail for you.

20:24.610 --> 20:26.570
It's from Valence.

20:31.090 --> 20:34.760
The whole deep state
paramilitary apparatus

20:34.960 --> 20:36.670
of the U.S. government
has been looking

20:36.870 --> 20:39.240
for this John Weir guy
for weeks now,

20:39.440 --> 20:43.200
- and-and they expect us to
believe they can't find him?
- [Benzo scoffs]

20:43.400 --> 20:45.290
- Man, they don't want
to find him.
- BENZO: Mm.

20:45.490 --> 20:47.640
Because as soon
as they find him,

20:47.840 --> 20:50.510
- we start to get answers, right?
- BENZO: Right.

20:50.710 --> 20:52.910
Answers about
what really happened

20:53.110 --> 20:54.690
- to Edward Homm.
- [Benzo scoffs]

20:54.890 --> 20:57.870
I'm gonna get those answers,
folks. My source,

20:58.070 --> 21:01.090
<i>Zaius, he said</i>
<i>he's gonna get me proof</i>

21:01.290 --> 21:04.220
<i>that Ed is not dead.</i>

21:04.420 --> 21:06.270
<i>And Edward Homm is</i>

21:06.470 --> 21:08.270
<i>the story here.</i>

21:08.470 --> 21:10.140
<i>The more I read</i>
<i>about this guy, I mean,</i>

21:10.340 --> 21:12.450
<i>you want to talk</i>
<i>about an American hero.</i>

21:12.650 --> 21:15.540
<i> Taking on fraud and corruption</i>
<i>in big business</i>

21:15.740 --> 21:18.110
<i> and government. Think about it.</i>
<i>Can you think of one</i>

21:18.310 --> 21:20.200
<i>other person in the last--</i>
<i>I don't know--</i>

21:20.400 --> 21:22.850
<i>- well, 2,000 years...</i>
- HOMM: That's too much, man.

21:23.050 --> 21:24.330
<i>SHAW: </i>
<i> ...that has done more to fight</i>

21:24.530 --> 21:26.200
<i>the evil and corruption</i>
<i>that is so...</i>

21:26.400 --> 21:29.030
Hailey, did you hear that?

21:29.230 --> 21:30.860
Morgan Shaw just keeps
talking about you, huh?

21:31.060 --> 21:33.820
He compared me to Jesus, and-and
that's a little much, right?

21:34.020 --> 21:36.390
I've heard crazier things.
How many viewers does he have?

21:36.590 --> 21:38.510
Um...

21:40.210 --> 21:42.390
2.35 million.

21:42.590 --> 21:44.350
- Woo-hoo!
- Woo-hoo.

21:44.550 --> 21:47.140
And it was just over 300,000
yesterday.

21:47.340 --> 21:48.660
Oh, my God, you're famous.

21:48.860 --> 21:50.530
Listen, I'm gonna go grab
something to eat.

21:50.730 --> 21:52.840
- Can I, can I get you anything?
- Um...

21:53.040 --> 21:54.100
No.

21:54.300 --> 21:55.800
- That's okay.
- Okay.

21:56.000 --> 21:57.800
<i>SHAW: I said it here.</i>
<i>I-I stand by it, too.</i>

21:58.000 --> 21:59.970
<i>You can tweet about that</i>
<i>all day long, listeners.</i>

22:00.170 --> 22:02.240
- Come on.
<i> -We're gonna get some letters.</i>

22:02.440 --> 22:04.280
<i>[train rumbling]</i>

22:04.480 --> 22:06.710
<i> [indistinct P.A. announcements]</i>

22:10.020 --> 22:12.410
One round-trip ticket
to Yonkers, please.

22:14.420 --> 22:16.330
[computer blipping, beeps]

22:28.040 --> 22:30.080
[exhales]

22:33.780 --> 22:35.310
Oh, hey. Hey?

22:35.510 --> 22:37.060
Oh, hey, Rasche.

22:37.250 --> 22:39.010
What are you doing slumming it
here in Financial Crimes?

22:39.210 --> 22:40.360
Because that's
where my files are.

22:40.560 --> 22:41.970
Which files?

22:42.170 --> 22:43.930
All the Bureau's info
on John Weir.

22:44.130 --> 22:46.670
But your archivist just told me
he can't locate any of it.

22:46.870 --> 22:48.580
Oh, that must be frustrating.

22:49.750 --> 22:51.680
If I find out that you're
hiding material from me

22:51.880 --> 22:54.550
that will help me in my
investigation, I swear to God...

22:54.750 --> 22:56.600
Well, if you're as effective
at investigating me

22:56.800 --> 22:59.120
as you are at investigating
the murder of Edward Homm,

22:59.320 --> 23:00.770
then I won't lose any sleep.

23:00.970 --> 23:01.980
[stammers]

23:11.390 --> 23:12.960
Anna!

23:13.160 --> 23:15.050
Hey, Anna,
do you know who sent this?

23:15.250 --> 23:16.920
Uh, just some delivery guy.

23:17.120 --> 23:19.520
Do you want me to call the store
and find out who sent it?

23:26.100 --> 23:28.240
No. Not just yet.

23:28.440 --> 23:30.400
♪

23:47.510 --> 23:49.550
You're the woman from the car.

23:54.650 --> 23:56.910
How do you know Weir?

23:57.910 --> 23:59.530
Dating app.

23:59.730 --> 24:02.180
No, seriously. I know everyone

24:02.380 --> 24:04.840
who works for Weir.

24:05.040 --> 24:07.450
I am someone
who cares about John Weir.

24:07.650 --> 24:08.970
Like you.

24:09.170 --> 24:10.410
[chuckles]

24:10.610 --> 24:12.500
- Like me? [stammers]
- Yeah.

24:12.700 --> 24:14.460
Lady, I don't know
what he told you,

24:14.660 --> 24:16.980
but he and I are
not exactly close.

24:17.180 --> 24:19.720
I don't know who Weir is to you,

24:19.920 --> 24:23.030
but I can only imagine
that he's Svengalied you

24:23.230 --> 24:25.080
into running some sort
of errand that is gonna...

24:25.280 --> 24:27.120
Weir didn't kill anybody.

24:27.320 --> 24:29.470
Oh. Oh, great.

24:29.670 --> 24:31.770
I have proof.

24:48.610 --> 24:51.670
John, I don't understand.
How is Miles sending you stuff?

24:51.870 --> 24:53.540
WEIR:
I don't know.

24:53.740 --> 24:54.980
Is he still alive?

24:55.180 --> 24:57.450
I don't know.

25:07.500 --> 25:09.990
♪

25:10.190 --> 25:12.640
It's got to mean something,
right?

25:14.600 --> 25:16.990
He wouldn't have risked
sending it to me if it didn't.

25:23.300 --> 25:25.480
Is this really necessary?

25:25.680 --> 25:28.260
I would not ask you
to wear them otherwise.

25:30.790 --> 25:32.830
Let's have a look.

25:41.490 --> 25:43.100
Sir?

25:44.100 --> 25:45.770
Agent Madi.

25:45.970 --> 25:48.250
My assistant says
you won't be put off.

25:48.450 --> 25:50.200
I don't mean to be a pest.

25:50.400 --> 25:51.900
Well, of course you do.

25:52.100 --> 25:53.980
Sometimes that's the only way
to get what you want.

25:54.980 --> 25:56.820
I have a teenage daughter.

25:57.020 --> 25:59.080
Maybe I learned from her.

25:59.280 --> 26:00.870
So I understand you've got
a real bug up your ass

26:01.070 --> 26:03.040
about John Weir.

26:03.240 --> 26:04.700
I assume from your persistence

26:04.900 --> 26:06.560
that means
you've found something?

26:07.820 --> 26:09.660
Yes and...

26:09.860 --> 26:11.830
no.

26:15.090 --> 26:17.100
What's this?

26:17.300 --> 26:19.570
Maybe you should just read it.

26:20.660 --> 26:23.050
You wouldn't believe me
if I told you.

26:25.750 --> 26:27.680
♪

26:27.880 --> 26:30.540
<i>[train rumbling, screeching]</i>

26:33.370 --> 26:35.460
Sorry.
[exclaims]

26:37.770 --> 26:40.910
- Hey, boss, you remember me?
- Fuck you, Kyle.

26:41.110 --> 26:43.340
Oh, you remember me,
I feel touched.

26:44.900 --> 26:46.570
Bang, bang.

26:46.770 --> 26:49.180
It would be that simple, Weir.

26:49.380 --> 26:53.090
Because I'm just
the task monkey, remember?

26:53.290 --> 26:55.230
If you try any
of these little tricks on me,

26:55.430 --> 26:57.320
- he said I could kill you.
- Who?

26:57.510 --> 26:58.930
Who would that be?

26:59.130 --> 27:00.620
Let's find out.

27:00.820 --> 27:03.180
Start walking, Weir, come on.

27:04.840 --> 27:06.880
[grunts]

27:15.500 --> 27:17.160
This is where I leave you.

27:17.360 --> 27:19.080
You know, I really wish

27:19.280 --> 27:21.080
you'd paid me more.

27:21.280 --> 27:23.040
You were a pretty good boss.

27:23.240 --> 27:25.200
You were a shit intern.

27:26.900 --> 27:28.950
That's true.

27:45.960 --> 27:48.050
What's in the box?

27:50.010 --> 27:52.370
Why didn't you let
the kid kill me?

27:52.570 --> 27:55.070
Killing you wouldn't
change anything, Mr. Weir.

27:55.270 --> 27:57.370
Or should I say Mr. <i>Wilson?</i>

28:01.280 --> 28:03.500
Yeah, your father,
I know all about that.

28:04.770 --> 28:07.210
Ben Wilson plays
a very sophisticated game.

28:07.410 --> 28:09.040
And, as usual,
he's playing it very well.

28:09.240 --> 28:11.080
You see, John,

28:11.280 --> 28:12.610
Ben is actually
the one who wanted

28:12.810 --> 28:15.090
the Shared Data Act passed,
not me.

28:15.290 --> 28:17.310
Arranging the assassination

28:17.510 --> 28:19.090
of Nora Evers
just to sway public opinion

28:19.290 --> 28:21.180
in favor of the Shared Data Law?

28:21.380 --> 28:23.910
That's pure Ben, John.

28:27.740 --> 28:30.320
Okay, let's just walk this back
a little further.

28:30.520 --> 28:33.110
Whose idea was it
for you and Miles Valence

28:33.310 --> 28:35.370
to spin off Arda from DBA?

28:35.570 --> 28:37.550
Arda, the company
that will soon have the most

28:37.750 --> 28:40.680
important and powerful
government contract in history?

28:40.880 --> 28:42.250
Whose idea was that, John?

28:42.450 --> 28:43.860
It was Ben, wasn't it?

28:44.060 --> 28:46.030
He manipulated
you and your friend

28:46.230 --> 28:48.770
into taking Arda public,
just so he could secretly

28:48.970 --> 28:50.430
buy up shares.

28:50.630 --> 28:52.040
And now that company has access

28:52.240 --> 28:55.610
to every single data point
of every single American,

28:55.810 --> 28:57.870
which they can weaponize
against all of us that fast.

28:58.070 --> 29:00.700
You just gave him that company,
John, for this moment here.

29:00.900 --> 29:02.870
- Your father is using you.
- Liar!

29:05.700 --> 29:07.740
[grunting]

29:14.010 --> 29:16.500
Someone's telling you
what to fucking say?

29:16.700 --> 29:18.320
<i>[voice crackling]</i>

29:25.150 --> 29:28.070
<i>CROWLEY:</i>
<i>Hello, John.</i>

29:29.500 --> 29:32.860
<i>I'm sorry I couldn't risk</i>
<i>meeting you in person,</i>

29:33.060 --> 29:35.940
<i> but my colleague laying on the </i>
<i> ground there should explain wh.</i>

29:39.380 --> 29:41.300
<i>I need your help.</i>

29:43.520 --> 29:44.960
<i>All you know about me</i>

29:45.160 --> 29:47.560
<i>is what Ben told you.</i>

29:48.610 --> 29:50.270
<i>I know this is difficult</i>
<i>for you to hear,</i>

29:50.470 --> 29:52.490
<i> but every move, every setback,</i>

29:52.690 --> 29:54.490
<i>every dead body,</i>

29:54.690 --> 29:56.840
<i>has all been Ben.</i>

29:57.040 --> 29:58.710
<i>Valence figured it out.</i>

29:58.910 --> 30:01.540
<i>Ben wasn't painting</i>
<i>a complete picture of things.</i>

30:01.740 --> 30:04.760
<i>Who was the last person</i>
<i>to speak to Miles</i>

30:04.960 --> 30:06.460
<i>before he jumped?</i>

30:06.660 --> 30:08.030
<i>The people you've lost,</i>

30:08.230 --> 30:09.860
<i> all you know about their deaths</i>

30:10.060 --> 30:12.380
<i>is what Ben told you.</i>

30:12.580 --> 30:14.640
<i>I've been tracking him.</i>

30:14.840 --> 30:16.510
<i>I almost had him, but somehow</i>

30:16.710 --> 30:19.040
<i> he blew up the AeroDelhi fligh.</i>

30:19.240 --> 30:21.950
You honestly think I'm gonna
believe you over my own father?

30:22.150 --> 30:24.910
<i>The man who abandoned you?</i>

30:25.110 --> 30:26.790
<i>And your mother?</i>

30:26.990 --> 30:29.310
<i>I am so sorry about Claire.</i>

30:29.510 --> 30:32.490
<i>I knew her. She didn't</i>
<i>deserve what Ben did to her.</i>

30:32.690 --> 30:34.710
<i>And you didn't deserve</i>
<i>what he did to you.</i>

30:34.910 --> 30:37.010
<i>I suspect that Ben told you</i>

30:37.210 --> 30:39.020
<i>the government gave him</i>
<i>no option,</i>

30:39.210 --> 30:41.800
<i>but you know that</i>
<i>your father had a choice.</i>

30:42.000 --> 30:43.760
<i>We always have the choice.</i>

30:43.960 --> 30:46.370
<i>And he chose</i>
<i>what he always chooses.</i>

30:46.570 --> 30:48.420
<i>His plan.</i>

30:48.620 --> 30:49.930
<i>His ambition.</i>

30:50.930 --> 30:52.670
<i>He chose Ben.</i>

30:54.330 --> 30:57.080
<i>I can prove</i>
<i>he's been lying to you.</i>

30:57.280 --> 30:59.120
<i>Do you know</i>
<i>where your father was living</i>

30:59.320 --> 31:01.860
<i>at the time</i>
<i>of the AeroDelhi crash?</i>

31:02.060 --> 31:04.560
Running around the world
chasing you.

31:04.760 --> 31:08.040
<i>He was living in a brownstone</i>
<i>three blocks from you.</i>

31:08.240 --> 31:11.000
<i>For a decade.</i>

31:11.200 --> 31:14.140
<i>As Dr. Benjamin Wolff,</i>

31:14.340 --> 31:16.880
<i>psychologist. Look it up.</i>

31:17.080 --> 31:20.190
<i>Your father wasn't</i>
<i>traveling the globe hunting</i>

31:20.390 --> 31:21.930
<i>a criminal.</i>

31:22.130 --> 31:23.880
<i>He was your neighbor.</i>

31:40.630 --> 31:41.900
So...

31:42.100 --> 31:44.070
what do we do next?

31:45.200 --> 31:47.470
Agent Madi, this...

31:47.670 --> 31:49.560
this file...

31:49.760 --> 31:51.740
this case...

31:51.940 --> 31:54.430
this is a real game changer.

31:56.210 --> 31:58.830
Thank you, sir.

31:59.030 --> 32:01.790
You can write the script for the
rest of your career with this.

32:01.990 --> 32:03.920
[chuckles softly]

32:05.530 --> 32:09.050
So I guess my only question
for you is...

32:11.490 --> 32:13.890
...what can I offer you...

32:14.090 --> 32:16.670
to make you forget
this file ever existed?

32:21.670 --> 32:23.640
[chuckles]

32:23.840 --> 32:25.720
Well, I thought you'd never ask.

32:29.680 --> 32:31.560
I'd like...

32:31.760 --> 32:33.480
my old job back

32:33.680 --> 32:35.640
in the Criminal Division.

32:37.780 --> 32:40.090
And I'd like to be made me
the head of the task force

32:40.290 --> 32:43.000
that's tracking down John Weir.

32:47.920 --> 32:49.960
That shouldn't be a problem.

32:53.440 --> 32:55.240
Oh, thank God.

32:55.440 --> 32:57.320
Where were you?

33:00.320 --> 33:01.770
What is this?

33:01.970 --> 33:03.770
It's from Valence.

33:03.970 --> 33:06.470
Piece of Gilgamesh,

33:06.670 --> 33:07.730
the story we obsessed over
when we were kids.

33:07.930 --> 33:08.950
Where's Ben?

33:09.150 --> 33:10.640
HOMM:
Um, not sure.

33:10.840 --> 33:12.910
He went out a while ago.
Didn't say

33:13.110 --> 33:14.680
- where he was going.
- Of course he didn't.

33:16.380 --> 33:18.430
HAILEY:
Oh, my God, John.

33:42.280 --> 33:44.320
♪

34:01.900 --> 34:04.130
HAILEY:
Weir, help me out.

34:04.330 --> 34:06.050
Why would Valence send you
a fossil?

34:06.250 --> 34:07.790
Some kind of code
I have to decipher.

34:07.990 --> 34:09.530
It's how we would communicate.

34:09.730 --> 34:11.520
It was his thing.

34:13.790 --> 34:15.190
Well.

34:15.390 --> 34:17.400
The gang's all here.

34:20.230 --> 34:21.930
So this was all just
an op for you?

34:22.130 --> 34:23.890
You've been running
an op on me, Dad?

34:24.090 --> 34:25.330
Jesus Christ!

34:25.530 --> 34:26.550
[Ben stammering]

34:26.750 --> 34:28.110
- Stop.
- BEN: Johnathan, breathe.

34:28.310 --> 34:30.120
- You need to breathe.
- Help me, God, shut up.

34:30.320 --> 34:33.150
Put that down, please, please.

34:42.730 --> 34:44.520
So this was all just
an op for you?

34:44.720 --> 34:46.480
You've been running
an op on me, Dad?

34:46.680 --> 34:48.220
- Jesus Christ!
- Weir, stop.

34:48.420 --> 34:50.570
Johnathan, breathe.
Y-Y-You need to breathe.

34:50.770 --> 34:52.920
No, you need to shut
the fuck up. I know everything.

34:53.120 --> 34:54.440
Johnathan, put that down.
You know you hate guns.

34:54.640 --> 34:56.050
Why don't you remind me,
where were you living

34:56.250 --> 34:57.660
- when the AeroDelhi flight
blew up?
- What?

34:57.860 --> 35:00.060
- I told you I was overseas.
- Liar!

35:00.260 --> 35:02.100
I've got proof that you were
living three blocks from me,

35:02.300 --> 35:04.450
- Dr. Benjamin Wolff.
- Look.

35:04.650 --> 35:06.540
All right, for a brief period,
yes, I was, but...

35:06.740 --> 35:08.500
All that time
I thought you were dead,

35:08.700 --> 35:09.680
you were living down the street?

35:09.880 --> 35:11.290
- Please.
- BEN: Oh, God.

35:11.490 --> 35:13.450
How do you know this?

35:15.240 --> 35:17.080
Crowley.

35:17.280 --> 35:19.510
Crowley? You found him?

35:19.710 --> 35:21.250
He found me,
and he said you were

35:21.450 --> 35:23.390
the real threat.
It's been you all along.

35:23.590 --> 35:25.340
BEN:
Oh, Johnathan, this is insane.

35:25.540 --> 35:27.220
WEIR:
No, no, no, what's

35:27.420 --> 35:29.130
been insane is what I've been
doing for the last few years.

35:29.330 --> 35:30.700
Listening to you,

35:30.900 --> 35:33.480
trusting you, pretending
like you cared about me.

35:33.680 --> 35:35.140
If you actually cared about me,
all you had to do was

35:35.340 --> 35:37.400
walk down the street
and knock on my fucking door!

35:37.600 --> 35:39.920
- You don't and you never will!
- No, Johnathan!

35:40.120 --> 35:41.670
I can't take back
what happened to you

35:41.860 --> 35:43.750
and your mother, but believe me
I never stopped caring...

35:43.950 --> 35:45.530
Shut up!

35:48.180 --> 35:50.800
You know this whole time you've
been trying to convince me

35:51.000 --> 35:52.370
that the only way to deal
with a real threat

35:52.570 --> 35:54.460
is drag it out into the light
and kill it.

35:54.660 --> 35:57.070
- I think you might be right.
- Put that down, please, please.

35:57.270 --> 35:59.900
HOMM:
John?

36:00.100 --> 36:01.640
<i>VALENCE: </i>
<i> You have to listen to me, John.</i>

36:01.840 --> 36:04.170
<i> John, I don't have any other wy</i>

36:04.370 --> 36:06.470
<i>- to contact you...</i>
- Don't you move.

36:06.670 --> 36:09.520
<i>...without exposing you...</i>

36:09.720 --> 36:11.520
<i>and Ben...</i>

36:11.720 --> 36:13.440
<i>and the whole plan.</i>

36:13.640 --> 36:16.780
<i>And I don't have much time,</i>
<i>so here goes.</i>

36:18.690 --> 36:21.310
<i>Crowley wants no loose ends</i>

36:21.510 --> 36:24.530
<i>in the Homm operation and...</i>

36:24.730 --> 36:27.960
<i>and he just ordered me</i>
<i>to kill you.</i>

36:29.880 --> 36:31.670
<i>Obviously,</i>
<i>I'm not gonna do that.</i>

36:31.870 --> 36:35.140
<i>Which means they will</i>
<i>definitely kill us both.</i>

36:38.580 --> 36:41.190
<i>He just fucking outplayed me,</i>
<i>John.</i>

36:43.110 --> 36:46.160
<i>I really thought that</i>
<i>I had figured everything out.</i>

36:46.360 --> 36:48.080
<i> That I could convince him that</i>

36:48.280 --> 36:49.950
<i>I was on his side</i>
<i>without ever actually</i>

36:50.150 --> 36:52.260
<i>being on his side,</i>
<i>but I don't know.</i>

36:52.460 --> 36:54.560
<i>He's got eyes and ears</i>
<i>all over Arda.</i>

36:54.760 --> 36:57.740
<i>Somehow, somehow he has</i>
<i>infiltrated my company.</i>

36:57.940 --> 37:00.870
<i>Sorry,</i>our <i>company.</i>

37:03.520 --> 37:06.010
<i>Listen, you're probably</i>
<i>on your way here right now...</i>

37:06.210 --> 37:08.190
<i>into this trap</i>
<i>that Crowley has set for you.</i>

37:08.390 --> 37:10.970
<i> But I-I might be able to buy yu</i>
<i>some time so you can escape.</i>

37:11.170 --> 37:13.230
<i>Because you and Ben,</i>
<i>you still got work to do.</i>

37:15.360 --> 37:17.200
<i>This plan of mine,</i>

37:17.400 --> 37:19.240
<i>it's a little fucked up.</i>

37:19.440 --> 37:21.420
<i>It's more than that, it's...</i>

37:21.620 --> 37:23.760
<i>really fucked up.</i>

37:25.110 --> 37:27.210
<i>If I told you what I was </i>
<i> gonna do, you'd try and stop m.</i>

37:27.410 --> 37:29.420
<i>Which I can't have.</i>

37:30.680 --> 37:32.560
<i>No matter what happens here,</i>
<i>I'm a dead man.</i>

37:32.760 --> 37:35.120
<i>But you still have a chance.</i>

37:38.080 --> 37:40.780
<i>I'm really sorry for what</i>

37:40.980 --> 37:43.180
<i>you're gonna have to</i>
<i>go through here.</i>

37:43.380 --> 37:44.830
<i>And I hope that you</i>
<i>can find somebody else</i>

37:45.030 --> 37:46.830
<i>that you can rely on.</i>

37:47.030 --> 37:49.650
<i>I wish to God</i>
<i>it could still be me.</i>

37:51.000 --> 37:53.060
<i>But I know you.</i>

37:53.260 --> 37:55.410
<i>And you are gonna be okay,</i>
<i>because you're strong.</i>

37:55.610 --> 37:57.710
<i>You're stronger</i>
<i>than you think you are.</i>

37:57.910 --> 37:59.670
<i>[laughs]</i>

37:59.870 --> 38:01.760
<i>What am I talking about?</i>

38:01.960 --> 38:03.550
<i>You're a fucking mess.</i>

38:03.750 --> 38:05.980
[laughs]

38:06.180 --> 38:08.730
<i>But if you're watching this,</i>

38:08.920 --> 38:11.280
<i>then it means </i>
<i> my little fucked-up plan worke.</i>

38:13.330 --> 38:15.120
<i>And you're okay.</i>

38:15.320 --> 38:16.780
<i>Gilgamesh.</i>

38:16.980 --> 38:18.940
<i>You must be okay.</i>

38:26.520 --> 38:29.130
<i>And that's the thought</i>
<i>that I'm gonna take with me.</i>

38:32.780 --> 38:35.360
<i>WEIR: Where do you go</i>
<i>to get a Gilgamesh tablet?</i>

38:35.560 --> 38:36.740
<i>VALENCE:</i>
<i>I've got a guy.</i>

39:05.640 --> 39:08.210
♪

39:19.870 --> 39:21.710
What the hell's going on?

39:21.910 --> 39:23.230
Jesus.

39:23.430 --> 39:24.710
John, you shouldn't be here.

39:24.910 --> 39:25.800
<i>YOUNG WEIR:</i>
<i>"When two go together,</i>

39:26.000 --> 39:26.890
<i>"each will protect himself</i>

39:27.090 --> 39:27.760
<i>and shield his companion."</i>

39:27.960 --> 39:29.980
"And when they fall,

39:30.180 --> 39:31.810
<i>- they'll leave</i>
<i>an enduring name." </i>
<i> -WEIR: "The trembling will leae</i>

39:32.010 --> 39:34.720
<i>"from your hand. Let your </i>
<i> courage be roused by the battle</i>

39:34.920 --> 39:36.890
to come."
[sniffles]

39:39.760 --> 39:41.460
He jumped to save me.

39:42.460 --> 39:44.950
HAILEY:
So those messages, they were...

39:45.150 --> 39:46.380
HOMM:
Crowley.

39:47.380 --> 39:49.220
If he infiltrated Arda, he...

39:49.420 --> 39:51.650
he had access
to all of Valence's data.

39:52.690 --> 39:56.050
He probably figured out
how you and Valence communicated

39:56.250 --> 39:58.000
and then pretended to be him.

39:59.960 --> 40:01.480
I'm so sorry.

40:11.800 --> 40:13.360
[sniffles]

40:16.500 --> 40:18.800
No more apologizing.

40:21.020 --> 40:23.380
Just tell me
that we're gonna work together

40:23.580 --> 40:26.340
to stop this motherfucker
once and for all.

40:26.540 --> 40:28.520
But I-I thought
you wanted to wait.

40:28.720 --> 40:31.210
I thought you said
it was too risky.

40:32.470 --> 40:33.350
Let me tell you,

40:33.550 --> 40:34.870
I know Crowley

40:35.070 --> 40:37.520
probably better
than anybody knows Crowley.

40:38.520 --> 40:40.010
God forgive me, I...

40:40.210 --> 40:43.130
I helped him devise
the Algorithms of Control.

40:46.400 --> 40:49.840
And right now the tenuous state
of our democracy

40:50.040 --> 40:53.410
is fertile ground
for a man just like him.

40:53.610 --> 40:55.280
Not just here--

40:55.480 --> 40:56.450
globally.

40:58.020 --> 40:59.720
Now, you've seen
what he is capable of

40:59.920 --> 41:02.730
when he had access
to Valence's data.

41:02.920 --> 41:05.640
Just imagine
what he's gonna be able to do

41:05.840 --> 41:08.590
when he has access
to everyone's data.

41:09.640 --> 41:12.910
He'll be able to manipulate
anyone and anything

41:13.110 --> 41:14.350
as he sees fit.

41:14.550 --> 41:16.260
Governments.

41:16.460 --> 41:18.700
Corporations.

41:18.900 --> 41:21.440
Markets. Armies.

41:21.640 --> 41:23.700
Take your pick. You name it,

41:23.900 --> 41:25.360
he'll infect it.

41:25.560 --> 41:27.530
And before long,

41:27.730 --> 41:29.970
we'll be powerless
to prevent him.

41:30.170 --> 41:32.890
So we have to stop him <i>now.</i>

41:33.090 --> 41:33.970
[sighs]

41:34.170 --> 41:35.580
Before it's too late.

41:35.780 --> 41:37.720
We have to stop him
while we have our free will,

41:37.920 --> 41:41.590
because that is
what we're in danger of losing--

41:41.790 --> 41:43.580
is our free will.

41:47.460 --> 41:48.810
Do you understand?

41:53.420 --> 41:55.040
[sighs]

41:55.240 --> 41:56.200
Johnathan?

41:58.470 --> 42:00.510
♪

42:08.700 --> 42:10.740
Whatever it takes.

